sometimes we have conflicts, when we are merging.
conflicts happen when:

the same line of code has been changed
in different ways in two branches.
                                  the line is different on two branches
                                  but it was same when these two branches were deviate

Note: this changes could be DELETION!
      if we delete a file on main,
      but it still exist on X branch,
      when we are mering X on main, we have conflict!

Note: this changes could be ADDITION!
      (add same file, but has different content!)
      it means when we create new branch as X, there is not a file like Y
      we add it later on main and X (with different content)

summary: we have conflict when a specif file on based point
         (when two branch has been deviate)
         are same, but it has some changes on "BOTH SIDE"

-----------------------------------------

in this situation we need specify what changes we have?
1.what we have on X
2.what we have on main
3.we need both of them

1.we create an empty file as "conflicts 9.2"
  and then make new branch from main as "conflict-branch"
  (so "conflicts 9.2" file is empty on both branch!)

2.we add different line on each branch separately
  "this line added on main"
  "this line added on conflict-branch"

Note: if we have some changes on X branch
      and move it to stage, then switch to Y branch
      and make a commit.
      we will have this changes on Y!
      (it possible just on new files, in existing file git does not allow to switch)
      (staged area is not related to branch, it's related to current working tree
       we could have some changes on stage, and by switching to another branch,
       the stage area get clean, because the stage (the changes we added)
       is compatible with new working directory)

3.when we want merge conflict-branch on main
  we have conflict on "conflicts 9.2":
                                      git merge conflict-branch

                                      Auto-merging src/section_4/conflicts 9.2
                                      CONFLICT (content): Merge conflict in src/section_4/conflicts 9.2
                                      Automatic merge failed; fix conflicts and then commit the result.

4.we solve the conflict by intellij UI
  when we counter the conflict, the intellij suggest "abort" or "resolve" on top left
  we choose "resolve"
  he open a window and list all conflicts (we have just one file)
  when we double click on it he opened "conflicts 9.2" file
  and allow us to choos witch one?
  we can choose the code on main, or the code on conflict branch!
  we choose both of them.
  (we can changed the order of these line)

5.after we apply changes
  we need a commit to make the merge. (conflict has resolved commit message)
  now the merge has been completed

Note: when we are choosing changes on UI
      we can do it manually, and adding some new lines!
      it's dangerous (we call it "evil commit"
                      because it add some line that not exist on any branches!
                      it add by  commit that just want to merge these branches
                      we should avoid it.
                      when we are resolving conflict, we should just resolving conflicts!)

Note: we could not solve the conflict by merging main on conflict branch at first!
      because the "conflicts 9.2" file exist on both of them,
      it generate conflict on this merging too!